placement Neil James Wilson Crawford examines the organization’s response to the growing number of refugees migrating to urban areas. Introducing a broader study of policy-making in international organizations, Crawford addresses how and why UNHCR changed its policy and practice in response to shifting trends in displacement. Citing over 400 primary UN documents, Crawford provides an in-depth study of the internal and external pressures faced by UNHCR – pressures from above, below, and within – that explain why it has radically transformed its position from the 1990s onward.UNHCR and global refugee policies have come to play an increasingly important role in the governance of global displacement. The Urbanization of Forced Displacement sheds new light on how the organization works and how it conceives its role in global politics today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aInternational agencies. 0aRefugeesxGovernment policy. 70(DE-588)4027366-00(DE-627)1062848430(DE-576)208970649aInternationale Organisation2gnd 70(DE-588)4056723-00(DE-627)1061539190(DE-576)209118741aStadt2gnd 70(DE-588)4063234-90(DE-627)1061286980(DE-576)20914789XaVerstädterung2gnd 70(DE-588)4113450-30(DE-627)1058293900(DE-576)209476583aEntwicklung2gnd 70(DE-588)4140484-10(DE-627)10562750X0(DE-576)209703180aDisplaced Person2gnd 70(DE-588)4436027-70(DE-627)2187774500(DE-576)212422189aPolitisches Mandat2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  a1951.  aAngelina Jolie.  aAntonio Guterres.  aConvention.  aEvaluation Policy Analysis Unit.  aGlobal South.  aIndia.  aIraqi.  aKenya.  aMajority World.  aNGO.  aSyria.  aUNHCR.  aUganda.  aUnited Nations High Commissioner.  aactors.  aarchival research.  acities.  aemergencies.  aevaluation service.  agovernance.  ah